ios envisaging the\nexistence of a distant, planetary-sized body and with the model-independent\nconstraints on them dynamically inferred from planetary motions. Thus, the\nissue of finding a satisfactorily explanation for the anomalous behavior of the\nMoon's eccentricity remains open.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Feb 2011 16:45:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 9 Feb 2011 14:46:55 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 21 Feb 2011 13:58:27 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 22 Mar 2011 15:47:40 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 27 Mar 2011 09:18:08 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Fri, 22 Apr 2011 13:59:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-07-26"}
